item.title: F5 Podcast Episode X3 - A Rocky Start
item.description:
Playing some rock and a touch of punk and some other random stuff. I also got a new pair of headphones prompting me to destroy a good portion of my music library due to "acceptable" audio quality not being good enough anymore.

Tracklist:

  1. Stanley Parable Soundtrack - Countdown (intro track)
  2. Kaiser Chiefs - Oh My God
  3. Franz Ferdinand - Take Me Out
  4. Rancid - Red Hot Moon
  5. Blur - Song 2 (Madeon remix)
  6. Computer Magic - Running
  7. LCD Soundsystem - All My Friends
  8. Wang Chung - Space Junk
  9. LCD Soundsystem - Pow Pow
item.itunes:subtitle: This time we have a grab bag of some rocks and one punk, followed by other stuff.

item.title: F5 Podcast Episode X2 - Lusine chill out speshal
item.description:
I have an intro track to use across all episodes, and decided to kick off with a really nice Lusine track, which then spiraled out of control into a Lusine-focused show of just a few tracks. I feel like this episode isn't that good, but that's why they're called experimental episodes. Feedback is appreciated!

Tracklist:

  1. Stanley Parable Soundtrack - Countdown (intro track)
  2. Lusine - Ask You
  3. Apparat - Fuse (talkie bit)
  4. Lusine - Gravity
  5. Lusine - Baffle
  6. Lusine - Double Vision
  7. There is music everywhere - Lowp (talkie bit)
item.itunes:subtitle: Experimenting with a chill out episode focused on a single artist.
